  "texts": [
    "[103] 2023 Text Summarization \"AI hallucination\" refers to receiving a response from the model when it lacks an appropriate answer, which appears to be the most likely summary of the study, despite its potential inaccuracy. 75 Meyer et al.",
    "[104] 2023 Academia \"AI hallucination\" can be defined as the capability of LLM-based chatbots to convey false information as though it were true.",
    "76 Hernigou and Scarlat [105] 2023 Health \"AI hallucination\" is a confident response that does not seem in concordance with its training data.",
    "77 Patil [106] 2023 Legal Setting \"AI hallucination\" is defined as a confident response by an AI system that lacks justification in its training data.",
    "These responses can appear factual but are not true, often simply being answers \"made up\" by the AI. 78 Alexander et al."
  ]
}